name: Flame Towers
description: {'Information:': ['The Flame Towers are among Baku\'s most famous landmarks, with their modern design reflecting the symbolism of the "Land of Fire." The towers represent Azerbaijan\'s urban development and illuminate the city\'s sky every evening with stunning light shows.'], 'Key Features:': ['An architectural design in the shape of flames, symbolizing fire, which is part of the national identity of Azerbaijan.', 'It contains the luxurious "Fairmont Baku" hotel.', 'LED night light shows completely cover the facades of the towers.', 'It includes commercial offices, residential apartments, and a shopping center.', 'Wonderful panoramic views of the Caspian Sea and the city of Baku.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['The best time to visit is in the evening to watch lighting shows on the towers.', 'You can stay at the Fairmont Hotel in the towers to enjoy unique looks.', "Don't forget to visit the nearby Bolivard walkway and take pictures with the towers in the background.", 'Wear comfortable clothes if you decide to walk in the surrounding area, especially at sunset.']}

name: Taza Pir Mosque
description: {'Information:': ['The Taza Pir Mosque is one of the oldest mosques in Baku, built between 1905 and 1914, and is an architectural masterpiece reflecting the classical Islamic style.'], 'Key Features:': ['Islamic architectural design adorned with Arabic calligraphy and geometric patterns.', 'A massive golden dome and two towering minarets.', 'It is located in a high-altitude area and offers a panoramic view of the city of Baku.', 'A quiet place for worship and also open to visitors.'], 'Tips for visiting:': ['Wear modest clothes when entering the mosque.', 'The best time to visit is early in the morning or afternoon to avoid crowding.', 'Photography is permitted in the external squares, but respect the privacy of worshipers inside the mosque.', 'Explore the surrounding area, where there are historical landmarks close to the Ashiri month.']}
short_description: Taza Pir Mosque is one of the oldest mosques in Baku, distinguished by its Islamic design and golden dome.

name: Icherisheher
description: {'Information:': ['A walled city that blends history and culture.'], 'Key Features:': ['The Palace of the Shirvanshahs: An architectural masterpiece dating back to the 15th century.', 'Maiden Tower: A historical symbol offering a panoramic view of the city.', 'Narrow alleys and stone buildings: a heritage atmosphere reflecting the old way of life.', 'Traditional markets (bazaars): display handicrafts, carpets, and Azerbaijani antiques.', "Museums and exhibitions: showcasing the region's history and traditional art.", 'Traditional restaurants and cafes: serving authentic Azerbaijani dishes.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['It is preferable to visit the place in the morning or sunset to enjoy photography and natural lighting.', 'Wear comfortable shoes, as the streets are paved with stones and are not suitable for uncomfortable shoes.', 'Do not miss the opportunity to shop in small markets to buy Azerbaijani carpets or manual souvenirs.', 'You can rent a tour guide to learn about the stories and the ancient history of the place.', 'Make sure to experience local food in restaurants inside the old city.']}
short_description: An ancient walled city in the heart of Baku, rich in historical landmarks and traditional markets.

name: National Museum of History of Azerbaijan
description: {'Information:': ["The National Museum of History of Azerbaijan is the country's largest historical museum, located in the palace of the merchant Haji Zeynalabdin Taghiyev in the capital Baku, and houses a vast collection of artifacts documenting the history of Azerbaijan from ancient times to the modern era."], 'Key Features:': ['It contains more than 300,000 artifacts, including old weapons, currencies, manuscripts, traditional clothes and jewelry.', 'Located within a stunning historical palace that reflects classic European architectural style.', "Distinguished exhibitions covering the stages of Azerbaijan's history, including stone ages, the Middle Ages and the modern era.", 'It provides indicative tours in different languages \u200b\u200bto explain the content of the exhibition.'], 'Tips for visiting': ['It is recommended to visit the museum early in the morning to avoid crowds.', 'Wear comfortable clothes because the tour requires walking between several floors.', "Don't miss visiting the Department of Islamic Antiquities and Ancient Manuscripts.", 'Photography is restricted in some areas, so inquire about the rules upon entry.', "It is recommended to use a guide or the available audio devices for a deeper understanding of the museum's contents."]}
short_description: The National History Museum displays the heritage of Azerbaijan from ancient times to the modern era.
